  "description": "Engagement-aware automation layer + self-contained timeframe system. v0.8.0 (MINOR v0.57.0 FA-5): canonical-vocab adoption per Frontmatter Alignment workstream. All 3 note templates (Daily/Weekly/Monthly Note) and 5 hub files + 4 prompt stubs now emit canonical `created_at:` (ISO+TZ; replaces legacy `created:`); discriminator tags `cowork-daily`/`cowork-weekly`/`cowork-monthly` stripped from templates (functional `daily`/`weekly`/`monthly` retained per _canonical-vocab non-discriminator status); Monthly Note canonical `month: \"YYYY-MM\"` introduced as parallel key alongside friendly `month_label:` (resolves cross-blueprint `month:` clash with finance); 12 of 13 rule_fragments declare `extends: _canonical-vocab` (SKILL.md fragment excluded — different schema); daily/weekly/monthly rule fragments drop `required_frontmatter.created` (extends covers); daily rule drops `required_tags: [{ tag: cowork-daily }]` (template no longer emits); monthly rule adds `month:` regex validation. Helper code unchanged this cycle — helpers already read `month_label` / `week_label` / file-name canonical keys. v0.7.0 (MINOR): cowork is now self-contained — NEW path convention spice/cowork/daily/YYYY/MM-MMMM/YYYY-MM-DD.md for cowork-owned daily notes; NEW CoworkDailyActions CustomJS class + Daily Note.md Templater template wire the create-flow; cowork-daily-hub-cards retargets from spice/daily → spice/cowork/daily (closes the daily-blueprint cross-reach); CoworkHubNav rewritten from BeaconCards 4-card row → AccentButton centered flex row (matches ScratchDayActions aesthetic), drops 'you are here', OMITS the current-hub button so each hub renders 3 buttons pointing at the other 3; universal nav-pattern (SpaceNavButtons → --- → CoworkHubNav → --- → content) across all 5 hubs + 3 note templates; Weekly/Monthly Note templates compute friendly H1 titles via Templater (Week 20 · May 11–17, 2026 / May 2026); Daily Note H1 (Thursday, May 14, 2026); Timeframes row grows 5 → 6 cards (Daily Hub | Today | Weekly Hub | This Week | Monthly Hub | This Month); NEW cowork-daily rule_fragment. v0.6.0 (MINOR v0.44.0): UX polish + character pass. v0.5.0: nav consolidation. v0.4.0: timeframe scaffolding. v0.3.0: 10 orchestrators + 28 sub-skills. v0.9.0 MINOR (v0.62.0 FA-9a): depends_on activity-feed >=0.1.0. Daily/Weekly/Monthly Hub grow Recent-Activity sections via ActivityFeed.render(dv, {scope, groupBy}) — cross-blueprint time-windowed feed over the canonical type:/created_at: vocab from FA-1..FA-7. NEW content/Today.md (cowork-today-hub) — curated landing surface with 4 sections (today's daily / today's meetings / today's scratches / today's project status changes) all via ActivityFeed; the 4th section uses useStatusChangedAt opt to switch the time-window comparison to status_changed_at. NEW rule_fragment for cowork-today-hub. v0.9.1 PATCH (v0.64.0): Daily Note template ownership returned to the daily blueprint (resolves template-destination collision; cowork's CoworkHubNav block is no longer injected into per-day notes — still present in hub files Daily Hub / Weekly Hub / Monthly Hub / Today / About Cowork / Cowork). Weekly Note + Monthly Note templates unchanged. v0.9.2 PATCH (v0.64.1): COWORK_CALLOUTS anchor switched from HTML-comment `<!-- COWORK_CALLOUTS -->` to Obsidian `%% COWORK_CALLOUTS %%` syntax — invisible in BOTH source AND reading mode. Updates: Weekly Note.md + Monthly Note.md templates; About Cowork.md prose; 5 orchestrator SKILL.md files (morning-briefing, midday-tripwire, eod-review, bootstrap-vault, ensure-daily-note); patch-daily-callouts SKILL.md (5+ literal-string references). Behavior contract unchanged — cowork orchestrators still locate the anchor by literal string match, just against the new syntax.",
